Business Brief -- WorldCorp:
   Concern Settles Tax Claim
   Resulting in Quarterly Gain
The provider of customized air transportation also
announced its plan to boost its stake in US Order to 40% from
33% with the contribution of $900,000 in working capital.
Through a series of purchase options, WorldCorp has the right
to own 100% of US Order, a provider of automated at-home
shopping and bill-payment systems.
   In late New York Stock Exchange composite trading,
WorldCorp shares were quoted at $12.125, up $1.